# Hilo People — frontend environment variables contract.
#
# Slice:  P01-S03-T002 — cross-origin / reverse-proxy topology (Phase 1 Auth + Data Foundation).
# ADR:    ADR-002 in TECHNICAL_GUIDE §15 — same-origin reverse proxy in dev and prod.
#
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# HOW TO USE THIS FILE
# Copy to frontend/.env (git-ignored) and fill in any values marked <CHANGE_ME>.
# In dev, most values here are valid as-is (default dev topology).
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# ─── API base URL ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# VITE_API_BASE_URL controls the prefix used by the auth httpClient for every
# backend call (POST /api/v1/auth/sign-in, GET /api/v1/users/me, etc.).
#
# EMPTY VALUE (recommended for dev and prod): frontend uses RELATIVE paths.
#   The vite dev server proxies /api → http://localhost:8000 (vite.config.ts
#   server.proxy, ADR-002). In prod, Nginx sits in front of the SPA and
#   proxy-passes /api → the backend container. The browser never knows the
#   backend's origin — same-origin topology in both environments.
#
# DO NOT set this to http://localhost:8000 in dev. That re-introduces a
# cross-origin XHR from the browser (:5173 → :8000), requires CORS preflight,
# and breaks the SameSite=Lax cookie contract documented in ADR-001.
#
# Ref: TECHNICAL_GUIDE §11.4 (cross-origin / reverse-proxy topology), ADR-002.
VITE_API_BASE_URL=

# ─── Verbose logging ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# VITE_ENABLE_VERBOSE_LOGGING enables auth feature console.info logs in the
# browser. Mirrors backend ENABLE_VERBOSE_LOGGING flag. Default true in dev
# so /verify-slice flows show the full hydration flow (AuthProvider, interceptors,
# redirect guards). Set to false in staging/prod.
VITE_ENABLE_VERBOSE_LOGGING=true
